nib.text:
The record high temperature for March 9 is 63F, which was set today at 3:15 p.m., according to the National Weather Service (NWS). The prior record was 61F, set in 1879. 

Wednesday's forecast is a high of 48F with a good possibility of rain throughout the day, however snow is unlikely. Temperature highs are expected to fluctuate between the high 40s and low 50s throughout the next week.
